15/08/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police announced on Friday (August 13th) they seized 90kg of heroin worth 26m euros at the Bajakovo border checkpoint with Serbia. 
The drugs were found in a car driven by a 44-year-old Dutch citizen of Turkish origin, who was travelling with his wife and three children. 
Police say they also found 1,180 packs of contraband cigarettes hidden in the family's luggage. 
An investigation is under way. 
(HINA, AFP, Vecernje Novosti, Blic, B92, Pobjeda - 13/08/10)
